  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_17",
    "text": "Figure 1: Kaplan-Meier survival plots of the overall actuarial survival according to the weight mismatch tertile group, from the time of operation to final follow-up. There was reduced survival among those in the lowest tertile group, log-rank p = 0.04.",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08067543057599656,
      0.5726686509293805,
      0.48405254101936973,
      0.6220930228786389
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 37
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_38",
    "text": "The mean period of ventilation post transplant was 302.7 h (SD 617.8), median 102 h (IQR298). On Spearman's rank correlation, this was not associated with the donor/recipient weight ratio (Fig. 3) (p =-0.12, p=0.14). Even when excluding the 11 patients who had been intubated for more than 100 h, there was no association (p = -0.10, p = 0.38) (Fig. 4).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.512195136038659,
      0.6090116282623494,
      0.9174483979200649,
      0.6919642857892929
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 38
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_18",
    "text": "tertile groups. Plotting survival to the end of the follow-up period (Fig. 2 and Table 3) showed that there was no statistically significant difference in long-term survival between the three tertile groups (log-rank p = 0.13).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08255159193761231,
      0.6453373015916358,
      0.4859286980121835,
      0.699156746146203
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 39
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_39",
    "text": "The mean period of ITU stay was 448 h (SD 749.2), median 184 h (IQR374). On Spearman's rank correlation, this was also not related to the weight ratio (p = -0.04, p = 0.58) (Fig. 5). Again, if the six patients who were in the ITU for more than 2000 h were excluded, there was still no association (p < 0.01, p = 0.98).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5159474772901548,
      0.6932043651387053,
      0.9174484138064759,
      0.76165674615326
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 40
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_19",
    "text": "Of the 104 patients who had received an ambulatory bloodpressure analysis during their follow-up period, 25 (18.4%) were hypertensive and receiving treatment for it. On Kaplan-Meier analysis of freedom from hypertension from the time of hospital discharge to date of last ambulatory blood-pressure measurement, there was no difference between the three weight groups (log-rankp = 0.39) (Fig. 3).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08442775880140398,
      0.702034883714263,
      0.4859287015057141,
      0.797965115825797
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 41
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_40",
    "text": "Extreme mismatch subgroup",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.5178236481042264,
      0.8066860467943261,
      0.7410881773648166,
      0.8212209298771853
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 42
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_20",
    "text": "Secondary outcome measures",
    "canon_role": "section_header",
    "bbox": [
      0.08410361184855758,
      0.8333853835318435,
      0.32102249929300425,
      0.8515268632510964
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 43
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_41",
    "text": "There were nine patients in whom the donor-recipient weight mismatch was 3 or greater (5.5%). By the end of the follow-up period, there was only 11% (1/9) mortality, compared with 18.2% (23/126) for those with a ratio of <3 (p = 0.76).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5159474695418448,
      0.8357558140679453,
      0.9174484138064759,
      0.8909883721551969
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 44
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_42",
    "text": "At the end of the follow-up period, of the six patients with 'extreme' mismatch who had been investigated with ambulatory blood-pressure measurement, only one was being treated for",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.5140713037718706,
      0.8908730158285106,
      0.9174484128074141,
      0.9317956347014109
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 45
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3_21",
    "text": "failure, in the middle group 24.5% and in the upper tertile group 28.8%; this was not statistically different (p = 0.48) (Table 3).",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.08442776874511854,
      0.9055059526104771,
      0.48405254133930903,
      0.9317956351536619
    ],
    "page": "scihub_j.ejcts.2011.04.042.pdf_3",
    "order": 46
  }
